  <!-- 
    The following invoicetypes section defines the invoice reports the tool will provide. The steps to 
    add a new one are:
    
      1. Create a new invoice report. The best way is to save one of the existing reports with a new
         name and then re-add the original to the project as an existing file. 
         
         DO NOT UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES SIMPLY COPY THE FILES AS THE CLASS NAMES WILL CONFLICT!
         
      2. Alter the invoice report as desired, save, and make sure the project builds.
      3. Add a new entry to the invoicetypes/invoices element below:
           3.1 The name attribute is displayed in the selection dialog boxes and should be English
           3.2 The key is stored in the [DWS No Rep Data].dbo.[RFS Invoice Type Data] table and should
               be unique within that table. A valid "carsub" value is also needed for invoice export
               functionality (an artifact of Jim B.'s accounting re-org).
      4. Run the application, change the type of an existing invoice, and see if the print preview
         works properly; Crystal Reports can be quite flaky in dealing with images.
  -->
